Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%grams}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the #pan{} and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef and Pork Mince{240%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

In a #bowl{}, mix together the @Burger Sauce{45%grams} and @Coleslaw Mix{120%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Drain the fat from the mince. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Beef Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Sugar for the Sauce{1%tsp}, @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliter} and @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp}.

Simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if it's too thick. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share your rice between #bowls{}.

Top with the spiced mince and slaw.

Sprinkle the cheese and @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} all over.

Enjoy!